Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine light red-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Name Lysimachos? From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0373.09.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0494)
